Reference Article:-    https://esc.sh/blog/what-to-do-when-your-computer-running-ubuntu-freezes/


When Linux(Ubuntu) freezes due to any APP or any other reason, then you can open 

Terminal by using the shortcut:-    ctrl+At+T


Then in the terminal type:-

                            pgrep application_name_which_has_frozen_linux

eg:-  pgrep unity

Then make a note of process id and kill the process by typing:-

                            kill process_id
                            
eg:- kill 7215
